Superoxide (O2

                           .-
                        ) concentrations were measured indirectly by an enzymatic colorimetric method employing the commercial kit Colestat for cholesterol quantification, Wiener Lab Argentina, determining [H2O2]. Calibration curves were performed using standard H2O2 commercial solutions. To that purpose, aqueous suspensions of the nanoparticles were photolyzed for 60 min in a quartz cell with light of 350 nm from a Rayonet lamp to allow for H2O2 accumulation. The irradiated suspension was centrifuged and 0.4 mL of the filtrate were added to 1.8 mL of Colestat reactant, the mixture was allowed to react at 37 °C for 5 min and the absorbance at 505 nm was measured.
